FBIS4-6665 "dreas077__a94006" FBIS-EAS-94-077-A Daily Report 21 April 1994 ANNEX Japan Keidanren's Hiraiwa Views Ties With U.S. Keidanren's Hiraiwa Views Ties With U.S. OW2104062994 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 21 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2104062994 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 21 April Morning Edition] [Text] Gaishi Hiraiwa, chairman of Keidanren [Japan Federation of Economic Organizations], commented on Japanese-U.S. relations, which have been troubled by Japan's trade surplus, and other issues at a news conference on 20 April. He said, "The two countries should compromise whenever possible, assert their views when necessary, and build a good relationship." He also stated, "We should build a sound bilateral relationship which is also acceptable from the European point of view." He asked the government not to give priority to the United States alone.
